## Why This Is Asked
This question evaluates offline-first routing with on-device compute, real-time edge-weight updates, crash safety, and cryptographic authenticity. It also tests SwiftUI/Combine integration and mobile performance optimization.

## Key Concepts
- **Graph algorithms**: A* with incremental weight updates
- **Offline-first data store**: SQLite with write-ahead logging for durability
- **Streaming ingestion**: Combine for processing traffic events
- **Crash safety**: Checkpoints and state persistence for reliable resume
- **Cryptographic verification**: CryptoKit for signed map updates
- **SwiftUI dashboard**: Route visualization with ETA and confidence metrics

## Code Example
```swift
// Graph structure
struct Node: Hashable { let id: String; let coordinate: CLLocationCoordinate2D }
struct Edge { let from: Node.ID; let to: Node.ID; var weight: Double }

class RoutingEngine: ObservableObject {
    @Published var currentRoute: [Node] = []
    @Published var eta: TimeInterval = 0
    @Published var confidence: Double = 0

    private var graph: AdjacencyList<Node.ID, Edge>
    private var checkpoint: RouteCheckpoint?

    // MARK: - A* with Checkpoint Resume
    func computeRoute(from start: Node.ID, to end: Node.ID) {
        let checkpoint = RouteCheckpoint(currentNode: start)
        currentRoute = aStar(graph: graph, start: start, goal: end, checkpoint: checkpoint)
        self.checkpoint = checkpoint
        updateETA()
    }

    func invalidateEdges(_ edges: [Edge.ID]) {
        guard let cp = checkpoint else { return }
        currentRoute = aStar(graph: graph, start: cp.currentNode, goal: goal, checkpoint: cp)
        updateConfidence()
    }

    // MARK: - Combine Traffic Ingestion
    private var cancellables = Set<AnyCancellable>()

    func subscribe(to publisher: AnyPublisher<TrafficEvent, Never>) {
        publisher
            .filter { $0.isSignificant }
            .sink { [weak self] event in
                self?.applyTrafficEvent(event)
            }
            .store(in: &cancellables)
    }

    private func applyTrafficEvent(_ event: TrafficEvent) {
        graph.updateWeight(edgeId: event.edgeId, weight: event.delay)
        invalidateEdges([event.edgeId])
    }

    // MARK: - Map Update Verification
    func verifyAndApplyMapUpdate(_ update: MapUpdate) throws {
        try CryptoKit.verify(update.signature, for: update.data)
        try applyMapUpdate(update)
        checkpoint = nil // Invalidate checkpoint after structural changes
    }
}
```

## Test Plan

| Category | Test Case | Method |
|----------|-----------|--------|
| Routing | A* finds optimal path on static graph | XCTest with known graph |
| Routing | Returns to checkpoint on weight update | Mock weight change, verify partial recomputation |
| Streaming | Traffic events update weights correctly | Combine test publisher, assert graph state |
| Offline | Route computed without network | Disable network, run computeRoute |
| Crash Safety | Resume from checkpoint after simulated crash | Inject crash state, verify recovery |
| Crypto | Reject tampered map updates | Modify signature, expect CryptoKit error |
| UI | Dashboard reflects route/ETA/confidence | ViewInspector snapshot tests |

